def: A person dwelling in, or having charge of, an infirmary, esp.in a monastic institution.
By the use of axioms; in the form of an axiom.
A name given to any one of several yellow or scarlet dyestuffsof artificial production and complex structure. In general they arediazo and sulphonic acid derivatives of benzene and naphthol.
The arrangement of feathers in definite areas.
The act of transfixing, or the state of being transfixed, orpierced. Bp. Hall.
Along or by the side; side by side with; -- often with of; as,bring the boat alongside; alongside of him; alongside of the tree.
